    "I was drowning in credit card debt — $34,000 across four cards at an average of 22% APR. The minimum payments alone were $780 a month, and barely $200 of that touched the principal. I'd been paying for three years and the balances had barely moved. Then a friend asked me a simple question: 'How much equity do you have in your house?' I'd never thought about it. Turns out, I was sitting on $120,000 in home equity while paying 22% interest on credit cards. I got a HELOC at 7.5% and paid off every card. My monthly payment dropped from $780 to $340. Same debt. Less than half the cost. I felt like I'd been robbed for three years — by my own ignorance.",
