    "I discovered HELOCs by accident — a podcast ad while driving to work. I pulled over and Googled it. Thirty minutes of research revealed that I had $110,000 in tappable equity in a home I'd owned for nine years. I was carrying $18,000 in credit card debt at 21%, paying $420/month and getting nowhere. The HELOC consolidated that debt at 7.5% — payment dropped to $215/month — and I still had access to $92,000 if I ever needed it. One podcast ad, thirty minutes of research, and my financial life changed.",
    "My parents never talked about money, so when I bought my first house, I had no idea what equity meant. Seven years later, my coworker was talking about her HELOC like it was the most obvious thing in the world. She'd paid off $22,000 in student loans using home equity at 7.8% instead of the 9.5% she'd been paying. I went home that night, looked up my home's estimated value, subtracted my mortgage balance, and nearly fell out of my chair. I had $95,000 in equity. I'd been paying 21% on credit cards while sitting on a fortune.",
    "We almost sold our house because we couldn't afford the repairs. The foundation needed work — $18,000. The HVAC was dying — $8,000. The windows were single-pane and drafty — $12,000. Total: $38,000 we didn't have. Then our real estate agent said, 'Why sell? You have $150,000 in equity. Get a HELOC, fix everything, and your home value goes up more than you spend.' She was right. We drew $38,000 at 7.5%, made all the repairs, and the home's value increased by an estimated $52,000.",
    "My daughter's daycare costs $1,800 a month. My wife wanted to build an in-law suite so her mother could move in and help with childcare. Cost: $45,000. We didn't have it. Personal loan quotes were 11-13%. Then I realized: we had $120,000 in home equity. A HELOC at 7.5% funded the entire addition. The $45,000 suite saves us $1,800 a month in daycare — that's $21,600 a year. The annual HELOC interest: $3,375. We're saving $18,225 net per year. The HELOC pays for itself in just over two years.",
