    "I was paying $2,100 a month across credit cards, a personal loan, and a medical payment plan. After taxes and mortgage, that left us about $800 for groceries, gas, and everything else for a family of four. We weren't living — we were surviving. A HELOC consolidated $48,000 of that debt at 7.5%. New payment: $950. We went from $800 to $1,950 in monthly breathing room overnight. Same income. Same house. One financial tool changed everything.",
