    "The moment that sold me on a HELOC was watching my neighbor's house transformation. In six months, they'd redone the landscaping, added a deck, and converted the garage into a home office. I assumed they'd come into money. Nope — HELOC. They explained that every improvement was funded at 7.5% and each one increased the home's value by more than the cost. They weren't spending equity — they were reshaping it. Their home went from a $310,000 listing to an estimated $380,000. All funded by the equity that was already there.",
    "My therapist — yes, my therapist — suggested I look into debt consolidation. She said financial stress was the root of my anxiety and insomnia. I'd never connected the two so directly. She wasn't recommending a specific product, but when I explored options, the HELOC stood out: lowest rate, most flexibility, and I already had the equity. Within a month of consolidating, my sleep improved. My anxiety dropped. My therapist said, 'You didn't need a new medication. You needed a new interest rate.' She was right.",
